occurrenceRemarks: DOR Ringtail west of Harper, Texas on U.S. 290  These are sometimes called "Ring-tailed Cat" but they are not a cat at al. They are in the family Procyonids, so relatives of raccoons. This species occurs in the American Southwest from Texas west to California. This is a nocturnal animal and I see road kills occasionally in this area (and sometimes even a live one!). The black and white ringed tail is longer and thinner than a raccoon's and the body generally paler. This one had been on the road for several days, unfortunately.
